```sh
# import an existing 1Password item
terraform import onepassword_item.myitem vaults/<vault uuid>/items/<item uuid>
```

onepassword:index/getEnvironment:getEnvi.description:
Use this data source to read environment variables from a [1Password Environment](https://developer.1password.com/docs/environments/). 1Password Environments allow you to organize and manage project secrets as environment variables. This data source is only supported when using **service account** or **desktop app** authentication; it is not available with 1Password Connect.

## Example Usage

<!--Start PulumiCodeChooser -->
```typescript
import * as pulumi from "@pulumi/pulumi";
import * as onepassword from "@1password/pulumi-onepassword";

// Read environment variables from a 1Password Environment.
// Requires service account or desktop app authentication (not 1Password Connect).
const example = onepassword.getEnvironment({
    environmentId: "your-environment-id",
});
export const envVariables = example.then(example => example.variables);
```
```python
import pulumi
import pulumi_onepassword as onepassword

# Read environment variables from a 1Password Environment.
# Requires service account or desktop app authentication (not 1Password Connect).
example = onepassword.get_environment(environment_id="your-environment-id")
pulumi.export("envVariables", example.variables)
```
```csharp
